WorldStage Newsonline– Morison Industries Plc, a company with leading portfolio of products that addresses cleanliness, chronic wounds, burns, 3rd degree burns, laceration and prevention of diseases has announced the resignation of Mr Deji Mustapha as its Acting Managing Director from December 31, 2020. Morison in a notification at the Nigerian Stock Exchange said its board had approved the appointment of Mr Adesoji  Akinola Oladejo as its Managing Director from January 4, 2021. The notification described Aladejo as a business process consultant with Tillbridge Limited He was described as a certified project management professional with over 25 years work experience in the business consulting among other qualifications.